A word is defined as a sequence of characters separated by spaces.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef count_words(s: str) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s` (str): A string that may contain letters, numbers, spaces, and punctuation.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the count of words in the input string.\\n\", \"code\": \"\\ndef count_words(s: str) -> int:\\n    return len(s.split())\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert count_words('hello world') == 2\", \"assert count_words('Hello World') == 2\", \"assert count_words('   ') == 1\", \"assert count_words('a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z') == 26\"] }"
